<article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_42089913" data-cid="42089913">
    <div id="comment_42089913">
        <header data-points="4" data-reason="Interesting">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Austrian economics"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Austrian economics<span> (4, Interesting)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~dytin" class="author" title="author name and user ID">dytin (517293) </a> | about a year and a half ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3272951&cid=42089913">(#42089913)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_42089913" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="4" data-reason="Interesting">
            <div class="comment-body">Bitcoin is the greatest real-world experiment in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austrian_School" title="wikipedia.org">Austrian economics</a> <span class="domain-text"> [wikipedia.org]</span> . For once we'll get to actually see if a "deflationary spiral" will actually occur when the rate of money creation slows, or if the Keyensians were just full of it.

Whether bitcoin actually succeeds or not, we'll at least get some really good data.</div>
