        <header data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:Austrian economics"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:Austrian economics<span> (1)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~Kergan" class="author" title="author name and user ID">Kergan (780543) </a> | about a year and a half ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3272951&cid=42090249">(#42090249)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_42090249" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="1" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>What you'd theoretically end up having, bitcoin or not, with an absolutely fixed amount of money and credit in circulation, is deflation if the population grows. The operating word here is money <i>and credit</i>.</p><p>The real question is whether bitcoin will get an kind of banking system from this or that point forward. If not, then deflation it will be, because more goods will be chasing less money; if so, then expect booms and busts like with any other fiat money, because bankers will be creating and destroying money in cycles.</p></div>
            <footer class="comment-footer" id="comment_footer_42090249">
                <div class="comment-footer-controls btn-group btn-group-sm" data-sid="3272951" data-cid="42090249">
                    <button class="btn btn-default call-form" data-sid="42090249" data-pid="42090249" data-cid="42090249"><i class="fa fa-reply"></i> Reply</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-default show-parent" href=""><i class="fa fa-level-up"></i> Parent</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-default menu-trigger moderatebtn"><i class="fa fa-gavel"></i> Moderate
                    
